One observation from today's trading: The "buy high and sell low" crowd was confidently buying today - based on the sites I cover. Many of the same who questioned covering $SPY short at $283 recently and felt volatility should not be embraced, have felt that the "action" was

indecisive until today or the day before. This approach of buying strength near the top of a trading range may work. Then, again it may not work. I am fading the market in the belief that the market is overvalued and the algos - who know everything about price and nothing

about value - have exaggerated the recent up move. I might be wrong but not for loss of logic of argument and analysis which is detailed everyday on @realmoney. Confident, no, considering the plethora of possible outcomes. Grandma Koufax always told me to avoid hubris

and to remember that the Cossacks might pummel us at any time. Laugh at my 12 Top Concerns today if you wish realmoney.thestreet.com/inde… but never forget that the only certainty is the lack of certainty.
